<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-05-03"><hi rend="italic">May 3,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President desires you to express through the appropriate channel his
                            deep appreciation of the touching message of His Excellency President
                            Loubet, on the occasion of the calamity in Utah, and his grateful sense
                            of the sympathy of the French people.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>